  "prompt": "Who is the inventor of calculator?",
  "response": "The invention of the calculator cannot be attributed to a single individual, as it has evolved over centuries through the contributions of many inventors and developments in technology. \n\nHowever, one of the earliest known mechanical calculators was the Pascaline, invented by Blaise Pascal in 1642. It was designed to perform arithmetic operations. Later, in the 19th century, Charles Babbage conceptualized the Analytical Engine, which is considered a precursor to modern computers.\n\nThe development of electronic calculators began in the mid-20th century, with significant contributions from various inventors and companies. For example, the first commercially available electronic calculator, the ANITA (A New Inspiration to Arithmetic), was created by the Bell Punch Company in 1961.\n\nOverall, while there are key figures in the development of calculators, it is a collective evolution rather than the invention of a single person.",
